Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; exterior: reserved; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, 8, is written in ink on the exterior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXII, no. 8)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 643, no. 10)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.436)
Condition: Part to right lost since Petrie 1886
